    "question_id" : 2608665,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This is the best way I found, to strip double quotes from the beginning and end of a string.</p>\n\n<pre><code>someString.replace (/(^\")|(\"$)/g, '')\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4739783,
      "reputation" : 630923,
      "user_id" : 3832970,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/IFOp5.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Wiktor Stribiżew",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3832970/wiktor-stribi%c5%bcew"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1482486812,
    "last_edit_date" : 1482486812,
    "creation_date" : 1482485029,
    "answer_id" : 41298589,
    "question_id" : 2608665,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>To remove one or more double quotes from the start and end of a string in Java, you need to use a regex based solution:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String result = input_str.replaceAll(\"^\\\"+|\\\"+$\", \"\");\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>If you need to also remove single quotes:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String result = input_str.replaceAll(\"^[\\\"']+|[\\\"']+$\", \"\");\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><strong>NOTE</strong>: If your string contains <code>\"</code> inside, this approach might lead to issues (e.g. <code>\"Name\": \"John\"</code> => <code>Name\": \"John</code>).</p>\n\n<p>See a <a href=\"https://ideone.com/aGh9hA\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Java demo here</a>:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String input_str = \"\\\"'some string'\\\"\";\nString result = input_str.replaceAll(\"^[\\\"']+|[\\\"']+$\", \"\");\nSystem.out.println(result); // =&gt; some string\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 14005810,
      "reputation" : 89,
      "user_id" : 10116014,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c77231541f1eb23ec0105c6d0d6f2a81?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Alex F",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10116014/alex-f"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1532202623,
    "last_edit_date" : 1532202623,
    "creation_date" : 1532202073,
    "answer_id" : 51459516,
    "question_id" : 2608665,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The pattern below, when used with <code>java.util.regex.Matcher</code>, will match any string between double quotes without affecting occurrences of double quotes inside the string:</p>\n\n<pre><code>\"[^\\\"][\\\\p{Print}]*[^\\\"]\"\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 535381,
      "reputation" : 4289,
      "user_id" : 904907,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d3901a22d358a7e8f27e4d01648903a3?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Ryan Amaral",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/904907/ryan-amaral"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 33,
